$>pip list OR pip3 list
List extensions installed for python 2/3
**for the current environment**
*may be different for a virtual environment*

$>python --version
Identifies python's current version

.bash_profile adds to $PATH environment variable so python3 can be used to access the interpretter from anywhere...
-- PATH="/Library/Frameworks/Python.framework/Versions/3.7/bin:${PATH}"
-- .bash_profile can be found at ~/user/<username>/.bash_profile

IDLE can be launched with:
$>python3 -m idlelib.idle

PYTEST Coverage run with:
$>pytest --cov-report html:cov_html --cov-module_name .
where:
  cov_html is the folder where the html report will be generated
  module_name is the module that will gets its coverage analysed
  . is the location of the module being analysed

